--------------------------------

### Real-time audio analysis with ffplay

Source: https://ffmpeg.org/documentation.html/ffmpeg-all

This command uses ffplay to create a real-time audio graph with an EBU scale meter set to +18. It takes an input MP3 file and outputs the audio stream with the meter applied.

```bash
ffplay -f lavfi -i "amovie=input.mp3,ebur128=video=1:meter=18 [out0][out1]"
```

--------------------------------

### FFmpeg Per-Stream AVOptions Example

Source: https://ffmpeg.org/documentation.html/ffmpeg-all

Illustrates setting per-stream AVOptions for audio codecs, including mapping, encoding to AC3 with a specific bitrate, downmixing to 2 channels, encoding to AAC, and setting a bitrate for the second stream using its absolute index.

```bash
ffmpeg -i multichannel.mxf -map 0:v:0 -map 0:a:0 -map 0:a:0 -c:a:0 ac3 -b:a:0 640k -ac:a:1 2 -c:a:1 aac -b:2 128k out.mp4

```

--------------------------------

### Capture Desktop Section and Encode with libx264 (FFmpeg)

Source: https://ffmpeg.org/documentation.html/ffmpeg-all

This FFmpeg command captures a specific section of the desktop defined by video size and offsets. It uses hwdownload to transfer frames from GPU to CPU memory, then encodes using libx264 with a specified CRF value, outputting to MP4. Explicit output format is required.

```bash
ffmpeg -filter_complex ddagrab=output_idx=1:framerate=60,hwdownload,format=bgra -c:v libx264 -crf 18 output.mp4

```

--------------------------------

### Convert Audio to CBR AAC with FFmpeg

Source: https://ffmpeg.org/documentation.html/ffmpeg-all

This example shows how to convert an audio file to Constant Bit Rate (CBR) AAC with a specific bitrate (64 kbps) and use the High-Efficiency AAC profile (`aac_he`). The `-b:a` option sets the audio bitrate, and `-profile:a` selects the AAC profile.

```bash
ffmpeg -i input.wav -c:a libfdk_aac -profile:a aac_he -b:a 64k output.m4a
```

ffplay -f lavfi -i "amovie=input.mp3,ebur128=video=1:meter=18 [out0][out1]"

*** Begin Patch
*** Add File: compress_videos.sh
+#!/usr/bin/env bash
+set -euo pipefail
+
+ROOT_DIR="${1:-.}"
+
+VIDEO_EXTENSIONS=(
+  mp4 mkv mov avi m4v webm
+)
+
+has_extension() {
+  local filename="$1"
+  local ext="${filename##*.}"
+  ext="${ext,,}"
+  for vext in "${VIDEO_EXTENSIONS[@]}"; do
+    if [[ "$ext" == "$vext" ]]; then
+      return 0
+    fi
+  done
+  return 1
+}
+
+while IFS= read -r -d '' file; do
+  if ! has_extension "$file"; then
+    continue
+  fi
+
+  if [[ "$file" == *"_compressed.mp4" ]]; then
+    continue
+  fi
+
+  dir="$(dirname "$file")"
+  base="$(basename "$file")"
+  name="${base%.*}"
+  out="${dir}/${name}_compressed.mp4"
+
+  if [[ -f "$out" ]]; then
+    echo "Skip (exists): $out"
+    continue
+  fi
+
+  echo "Compressing: $file"
+  ffmpeg -hide_banner -nostdin -i "$file" \
+    -map 0:v:0 -map 0:a? \
+    -c:v libx264 -preset slow -crf 22 -profile:v high -pix_fmt yuv420p \
+    -vf "scale='min(1920,iw)':'min(1080,ih)':force_original_aspect_ratio=decrease" \
+    -c:a aac -b:a 128k \
+    -movflags +faststart \
+    "$out"
+done < <(find "$ROOT_DIR" -type f -print0)
+
+echo "Done."
*** End Patch

payload.input:
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: compress_videos.sh
@@
 VIDEO_EXTENSIONS=(
   mp4 mkv mov avi m4v webm
 )
 
+CRF=26
+AUDIO_BITRATE="96k"
+
 has_extension() {
   local filename="$1"
   local ext="${filename##*.}"
   ext="$(printf '%s' "$ext" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')"
@@
   return 1
 }
 
+get_size_bytes() {
+  if stat -f%z "$1" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
+    stat -f%z "$1"
+  else
+    stat -c%s "$1"
+  fi
+}
+
 while IFS= read -r -d '' file; do
   if ! has_extension "$file"; then
     continue
@@
   if [[ -f "$out" ]]; then
     echo "Skip (exists): $out"
     continue
   fi
 
+  in_size="$(get_size_bytes "$file")"
+
   echo "Compressing: $file"
   ffmpeg -hide_banner -nostdin -i "$file" \
     -map 0:v:0 -map 0:a? \
-    -c:v libx264 -preset slow -crf 22 -profile:v high -pix_fmt yuv420p \
+    -c:v libx264 -preset slow -crf "$CRF" -profile:v high -pix_fmt yuv420p \
     -vf "scale='min(1920,iw)':'min(1080,ih)':force_original_aspect_ratio=decrease" \
-    -c:a aac -b:a 128k \
+    -c:a aac -b:a "$AUDIO_BITRATE" \
     -movflags +faststart \
     "$out"
+
+  out_size="$(get_size_bytes "$out")"
+  if [[ "$out_size" -ge "$in_size" ]]; then
+    echo "Skip (no savings): $out"
+    rm -f "$out"
+  fi
 done < <(find "$ROOT_DIR" -type f -print0)
*** End Patch
